(1, 'http://laracms.local/cms_assets/front_page/managements/team-1.jpg', 'A. Rouf Chowdhury', 'Chairman', 'Mr. Abdur Rouf Chowdhury is a graduate in Business Management from the Massachusetts institute of Technology, USA. He has a wide range of experience in several industries including Auto Mobile, Telecom, Pharmaceuticals and Petroleum. He was the Resident Manager of Two American Pharmaceutical companies In Bangladesh. Being the Senior Management position in Jamuna Oil Company he contributed for 15 years in the Market Development of Petroleum products in Bangladesh. Both Rangs & Sea Recourses groups comprised of 32 companies were formed under his dynamic leadership. The huge success of 32 companies of the Two Groups during a short span of time is an ample proof of his dynamic leadership and progressive mind. Currently he is the Chairman of Bank Asia Limited. He also has his dynamic foothold in the print media; he is the Director of renowned English Daily ‘The Daily Star’ and chairman of Bengali Daily ‘Shokaler Khabar’.', 'http://laracms.local/pages/chairman', 1, '2021-09-19 17:15:16', '2021-10-14 11:08:25'),
(2, 'http://laracms.local/cms_assets/front_page/managements/team-2.jpg', 'Nafees Khundker', 'Director', 'Nafees Khundker has worked in Banking & Finance industry for more than 20 years specializing in Corporate & Investment Banking and Transaction Banking, with Deutsche Bank and Standard Chartered. His last role in Banking was as Managing Director & the Head of Commercial Banking Sales for ASEAN with Standard Chartered based out of Singapore.\n\nHis finance related expertise is in dealing with large Corporates and Financial Institutions clients (Asia Pacific and Middle East), working on Corporate Finance, Transaction Banking and Financial Markets products. He has also worked on strategic partnerships with financial institutions clients for white labeling of cash management and FX platforms. He has built businesses in the region, which include building teams, systems, risk management and processes.\n\nNafees has investments and board oversight in various companies in retail, distribution, finance and Information Technology. He has invested in and turned around quite a few businesses in technology, retail, automobiles and distribution sectors. Nafees has a special interest in sustainability initiatives and works with small nonprofit organizations. He is an avid sportsperson with particular interest in tennis, golf and cricket.', 'http://laracms.local/pages/director', 2, '2021-09-19 17:30:48', '2021-10-14 11:08:41'),
(3, 'http://laracms.local/cms_assets/front_page/managements/team-3.jpg', 'Md. Serajul Islam, FCMA', 'Chief Executive Officer', 'Mr. Md. Serajul islam completed his graduation and post graduation from Dhaka University. After completion of his post-graduation, he completed Professional Course \'Cost and Management Accountants\' from ICMAB, he achieved Diploma in Association of Bankers, Bangladesh (DAIBB) in 2004. He completed an international course on Business Innovation by Information Technology (BIIT), from AOTS, Japan and \"Advanced Management Executive Program-Education\" course from The University of Hong Kong.\n\nPrior to joining ERA-InfoTech Limited, As the Chief Executive Officer Mr. Md. Serajul Islam started his banking career as Financial Analyst in Sonali Bank Limited. Later, he served Bank Asia Limited as the Deputy Head of ICT department as well as Business Analyst.\n\nHe is also involved in the largest Poverty Alleviation Project of Bangladesh Government “Ektee Bari Ektee Khamar (EBEK)”. With his leadership skills and sound technical knowledge, the automation of this specialized Micro Finance Management project which brings marginal mass people under the financial inclusion through the optimum utilization of ICT innovation has been successfully completed.', 'http://laracms.local/pages/chief-executive-officer', 3, '2021-09-19 17:32:47', '2021-10-14 11:09:01');
